WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.540
I'm going to talk a little bit about novel hepcidin modulators in polycythemia vera.

00:00:08.620 --> 00:00:13.120
This is an area of a lot of excitement in MPN.

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:14.880
So let's get started.

00:00:17.320 --> 00:00:18.220
All right.

00:00:18.300 --> 00:00:23.580
Unlike in myelofibrosis, hepcidin levels are actually decreased in PV.

00:00:24.360 --> 00:00:32.680
And this is a result of the expanded erythropoiesis that occurs in PV to support the production

00:00:32.680 --> 00:00:40.680
of red blood cells due to constitutive JAK stat signaling, and also iatrogenically through

00:00:40.680 --> 00:00:42.100
therapeutic phlebotomy.

00:00:42.100 --> 00:00:52.000
So hepcidin levels are decreased, which means that you have increased iron absorption and

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.100
increased iron release from...

00:00:54.360 --> 00:01:01.520
macrophages that are basically being funneled into the bone marrow to support the development

00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:03.480
of new red blood cells.

00:01:04.300 --> 00:01:08.300
So in untreated PV, you'll have low hepcidin levels.

00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:15.080
And then with hepcidin memetics, the goal is to really increase hepcidin levels, and

00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:18.340
that actually promotes normalization of the hematocrit.

00:01:20.220 --> 00:01:24.300
So hepcidin memetics like resveratide and also inhibitors...

00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:32.340
So these inhibitors of TMPRSS6 promote degradation of ferroportin, which is the only iron exporter

00:01:32.340 --> 00:01:33.340
in cells.

00:01:33.340 --> 00:01:43.680
And so TMPRSS6 is a protease on the cell surface that inhibits BMP and SMAD signaling and is

00:01:43.680 --> 00:01:49.560
a negative regulator of hepcidin production in hepatocytes.

00:01:49.560 --> 00:01:52.300
And so when you inhibit a negative regulator of hepcidin, you actually inhibit the production

00:01:52.300 --> 00:01:53.300
of hepatocytes.

00:01:53.300 --> 00:01:54.300
And so when you inhibit a negative regulator of hepcidin, you actually inhibit the production

00:01:54.300 --> 00:01:55.300
of hepatocytes.

00:01:55.300 --> 00:01:56.300
And so when you inhibit a negative regulator of hepcidin, you actually increase hepcidin

00:01:56.300 --> 00:01:57.300
levels.

00:01:57.300 --> 00:02:02.140
And then, of course, hepcidin and hepcidin memetics bind to and degrade ferroportin directly,

00:02:02.140 --> 00:02:06.400
which is, like I mentioned, an iron export protein.

00:02:06.400 --> 00:02:11.520
Increasing hepcidin levels leads to decreased dietary iron absorption, reduced iron release

00:02:11.520 --> 00:02:18.020
from macrophages, and ultimately the goal, which is reduced erythropoiesis and restoration

00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:22.280
of iron homeostasis in PV.

